Eight Prompt: (Main)
Build a Roadmap Feature in a React + Vite portfolio project with the following architecture and behavior:

Core Requirements
Create a Roadmap Section (page/component) to display multiple skill roadmaps.
Each roadmap should be represented as a card component (title, short description).
Roadmaps should be data-driven (stored in JSON or a JS object for easy updates).
Navigation
Use React Router for navigation.

Clicking a roadmap card should route to:

/roadmap/:skillName
Detailed Roadmap Page
Build a RoadmapDetail component that:
Dynamically loads roadmap data based on route params.
Displays:
Skill title
List of topics/modules
Nested subtopics (if any)
Notes Section
Each topic should support a deep notes section:
Expandable/collapsible UI (accordion or tabs)
Supports formatted content (text, code snippets, links)
Optional: Store notes separately and map them to topics.
Suggested Folder Structure
src/
 ├── components/
 │    ├── RoadmapCard.jsx
 │    ├── RoadmapList.jsx
 │    ├── TopicAccordion.jsx
 │
 ├── pages/
 │    ├── Roadmaps.jsx
 │    ├── RoadmapDetail.jsx
 │
 ├── data/
 │    ├── roadmaps.js
 │
 ├── router/
 │    ├── AppRouter.jsx
Data Example
export const roadmaps = [
  {
    id: "react",
    title: "React Roadmap",
    description: "Frontend development with React",
    topics: [
      {
        title: "Basics",
        notes: "JSX, components, props, state"
      },
      {
        title: "Advanced",
        notes: "Hooks, performance optimization"
      }
    ]
  }
];
UI/UX Expectations
Responsive layout (grid for roadmap cards)
Clean and minimal design
Easy to add/edit roadmap data without changing components

